Introduction

Base URL: http://pay.hst-et.com

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Authenticating requests

This API is not authenticated.

Endpoints

Handle an incoming registration request.

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://pay.hst-et.com/api/v1/register" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"name\": \"kfxwizxhxncgmrlwohywr\",
    \"email\": \"joshua.zieme@example.net\",
    \"password\": \"est\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://pay.hst-et.com/api/v1/register"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "name": "kfxwizxhxncgmrlwohywr",
    "email": "joshua.zieme@example.net",
    "password": "est"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request      

POST api/v1/register

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

name   string   

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: kfxwizxhxncgmrlwohywr

email   string   

Must be a valid email address. Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: joshua.zieme@example.net

password   string   

Example: est

Handle an incoming authentication request.

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://pay.hst-et.com/api/v1/login" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"email\": \"reichel.ward@example.com\",
    \"password\": \"n~8g)+.\'Z\'7[q5AG:&#(\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://pay.hst-et.com/api/v1/login"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "email": "reichel.ward@example.com",
    "password": "n~8g)+.'Z'7[q5AG:&#("
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Example: application/json

Must be a valid email address. Example: reichel.ward@example.com

Example: n~8g)+.'Z'7[q5AG:&#(

Handle an incoming new password request.

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://pay.hst-et.com/api/v1/reset-password" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \

    \"email\": \"heller.mathilde@example.net\",
    \"password\": \"dolorem\"
}"

);

    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",

Mark the authenticated user's email address as verified.

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://pay.hst-et.com/api/v1/verify-email/est/ut" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://pay.hst-et.com/api/v1/verify-email/est/ut"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
